There has been much precident for nerfing an entire zone because of a single class ability in the past... don't think it won't happen again.  The way the new pathing works, and the way the Bards work, it's only able to work in that zone. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I dont agree with his extreme opinion that we are broken, I do agree that wizards are one of the least favorite group members of the bunch. As an experiment I turned LFG on for a few weeks even though I wasn't actually LFG (camping quest mobs, solo, etc). In the first week I played almost daily for at least 4hr sessions. I think I had 2, maybe 3 tells from groups wanting me to join them.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Heh, do you think people actually do /who LFG all?  No, they don't.  If you're not actively looking for a group you most likely won't find one... period.  I've never been in a single group where we've done a /who LFG all to find a group member, we always wait until people either ask us to join or until we see them in shout.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>One simple question. Why didn't they just nerf whatever song bards were using to do that, if that was their intent?<br>
Clearly, their intent is to nerf overall soloing, since the change they made affects all.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Like I said, if you don't understand the situation you probably shouldn't comment on it.  Did you look into how they did the kiting?  It would involve nerfing around 6 spells and 2 AA abilities.  Nerfing a series of spells because a few members of a class can do something obviously very overpowered as opposed to nerfing the zone would cause many, many more problems than it would solve.  Their only choice in this situation was to nerf a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>single zone</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  <br>
<br>
Think of it another way.  Hypothetical situation; a few Wizards are using various quad kiting spells to somehow kill 30 mobs in 25 minutes gaining 6 AA per pull in Plane of Time... SoE sees this and says &quot;hey now, that's bad!&quot;  After looking over it they apply a patch that nerfs Atol's and every quad spell 51+ instead of PoTime soloing, would that be OK with you?  That's basically what you want done for Bards.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Another point.. since this change does render this, and any other similarly nerfed areas useless for soloing, it puts even more people into the other areas, like PoS.. Can't speak for your server, but even at 6:30 am EST, those froggies are usually camped. We can't afford to lose ANY places that you can fight in without the holy trinity.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
As previously pointed out there are still many places to solo.  It's not impossible to get a group either, and it most certain is very easy to make one yourself. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Verdana;font-size:xx-small;">Officer of Triton, Member of Team Ice, Povar<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->:. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=458434">Rombus, Arcanist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> .:. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5702">Rommy, 61 High Priest</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> .:</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwideonthegnome>GwideonTheGnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 104<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/03 3:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: One question, Rombus</span><hr size=1> Gnomish Greetings!<br>
