Guess what, I'm level 48. I have NO AA abilities. I have one flowing thought item, the earring of the solstice. At 49 I get the next familiar with 1 tick mana regen. With food, i now have an INT of 249. I have extended range 3, improved damage 3, spell haste 2, enhancement haste 2. All of which I earned or bought. <br>
<br>
My wizard is the first toon I every created. And since I didn't know what I was doing, I started him with an INT of 90! Yes, 90!. I didn't know that the amount of mana was based on INT. And I have survived with this all the way up to 48 and flourished. My friends all call me the best wizard they hav ever know. And some of them have been playing for years. Since EQ came out.<br>
<br>
I hardly ever go OOM. As I figure it, I have 2500 mana. And I'm working on getting my INT to 255 without food. I often see a Staff of the Morning Dew for sale in the bazaar (FV server, not much is No Drop). As soon as I save up enough, I'm buying myself one. After that, I'm focusing on DEX and AGI pieces. <br>
<br>
If you want improved damage, get yourself one of those new Robes of Tempest, which are player made. I got one for 20k. Yes, that's right, a level 48 player had 20k to spare. And I still have lots of money in the bank.<br>
<br>
Am I in a guild? You bet! Guess what, it's a guild I STARTED WITH MY BEST FRIEND IN GAME! Since I lead this guild, that means I'm not sitting around waiting for a raid to happen, I'm making them happen. I'm turning into a pretty good raid leader too. <br>
<br>
But see, the bottom line is, I'm working at it. Not complaining and not wanting others to do for me. And I'm not some super level 65 maxxedAA wizard. I'm a level 48 wizard that loves being a wizard! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rombusmindspire>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 6848<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/03 9:58 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Get a clue</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>They do not need to do a /who all LFG my friend. The new LFG tool makes it very easy to /tell PrimeGroupingClass several zones away to join you where they are, especially in PoP where an exp group is 2 zones away for those classes in high demand. I have done it myself when the slower logs and we need a replacement. Last night I got a group from a Wizard logging for the night and when our slower logged I prodded the group to add a 65 Wizard instead of a slower (none in zone and I figured our DPS was sufficient to kill mobs w/o a slower). I go a resounding /no_dice.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
