<br>
I have an idea here for exp'ing: start a big write-in campaign, and demand that SOE set up a couple of zones at the high levels, for those who PREFER to solo, to go hunt in. Why not..? Why is forced grouping automatically &quot;the point&quot; of this game..? To further increase revenues for SOE..? Personally, I prefer grouping... but others may not. Fine, then set up an optional area for them to go solo in SAFELY... and WITHOUT pulling occasional, out of control trains all over the other players who just zoned in to the graveyard (like Druids seem to always do to *me* when I pop in to PoN). I see nothing imbalanced or otherwise &quot;wrong&quot; about having optional solo areas in the game for those who can do so. And the exp per kill could be adjusted accordingly to make grouping a still more attractive (but not the ONLY) possibility for leveling, doing AA grinds, or whatever.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp...<br>
